# ── Security headers, applied to every response ─────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Pages applies these to all paths when listed against `/*`.
# Deliberately conservative — only headers whose worst-case failure mode
# is "one feature stops working" rather than "the whole site breaks":
#
#   X-Content-Type-Options    prevent MIME-sniffing the contents of a file
#   Referrer-Policy           don't leak full path history to third parties
#   X-Frame-Options           cheap clickjacking defence
#   Permissions-Policy        only geolocation is needed; deny everything else
#
# HSTS is NOT set here — enabled at the Cloudflare zone level in SSL/TLS
# settings so the browser honours the commitment even if this file lies.
# CSP is deliberately omitted: tightening it without breaking the map
# (Mapbox CDN) or the analytics beacon (cloudflareinsights.com) needs its
# own rollout and testing cycle.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(self), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), magnetometer=(), gyroscope=(), accelerometer=()

# Vite hashed assets — immutable, cache forever
/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

# Static images, icons, manifest
/*.png
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
/*.svg
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
/*.ico
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400

# PMTiles — weekly refresh
/data/*.pmtiles
  Access-Control-Allow-Origin: *
  Access-Control-Expose-Headers: Content-Length, Content-Range, Accept-Ranges
  Content-Type: application/octet-stream
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=604800, no-transform
